/ : The base of the linux directory is the root. This is the starting point of FSH. Every directory arises from the root directory. It is represented by a forward (/)
/ root : It is the home directory for the root user (superuser)
/bin (user Binaries) :  contains binary executable.Comman linux cammand you need the use in single-user modes are located under this directory.Cammands used by all the users of the system are located here
/div(Device Files) : It contains hardware device files, Contains device files, These include terminal devices, usb, or any device attached to the system.
/Var (Variable Files) : The variable data files such as log files are located in the /var directory. Files contents that tend to grow are located in this directory. 
. /var/log : System log files generated by OS and other application.
.  /var/lib : contains database and package files.
.  /var/mail : Conatins Emails.
.  /var/tem : Contains temporary files needed for reboot

/mnt (Mount Directory) : This directory is used to mount a files system temporarily.
/media (Removable media Devices) : The /media directory contains subdirectory where removable media devices inserted into the computer are mounted.
/usr(user binaries) : The /usr directory contains application and files used by users, as apposed to application and files used by the system.
/etc (configuration files) : It contains all configuration files of server.The core configuration files are stored in the /etc directory. It controls the behavior of an operation system or application. This directory also contains atartup and shutdown programscript.
/boot (boot loader files) : The /boot directory contains the files needed to boot the system, The GRUB boot loader files and your linux kernals are stored here.
/opt (optional application) : The opt directory is used for installing the application software from third- party vendors that are not availables in the linux distribution. Usually, the software code is stored in the opt directory and the binary code is linked to the bin directory so that all user can run that software
/home (Home directory) : It contains secondary users home directory.
/tem (Temporary files) : Directory that contains temporary files created by system and users, Files under this directory are deleted when system is rebooted.


     Basic commands
pwd : it shows the present working dorectory 
ls : it shows available files and directory list in the present working directory.
uname : it shows the name of the kernel (os) 
cd : it shows version of the kernel
clear it use for clear screen 
whoami : it show currently login user name 
history : it show list of previously used cammands
date : it show time and date

Create files or directory
For create signal directory
. mkdir / Homescoopers
For create multiple directory 
.  mkdir / Homescoopers qa test
For create directory path (directory inside directory)
